<placeName cert="high" full="yes">Oxyrhynchus</placeName></head><div lang="grc" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="edition"><div n="r" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="1"/>Ἀπολλώνιος Ἀρτεμᾷ τῷ ἀδελφῷ χαίρειν. 

    <lb n="2"/>πρὸ μὲν παντὸς <choice><corr>εὔχομαι</corr><sic>ευχομε</sic></choice> πᾶσι τοῖς θεοῖς τὰ ἐν βίῳ 

    <lb n="3"/>σοι κάλλιστα ὑπαρχθῆναι· καὶ νῦν τῷ ἀδελ-

    <lb n="4"/>φῷ σου ἔδωκα <expan><ex cert="high">δραχμὰς</ex></expan> <num value="500">φ</num> καὶ τῷ Πτολεμαίῳ ἤδη 

    <lb n="5"/>μετεβαλόμην ἀπὸ μέρους, καθὼς ἠθέ-

    <lb n="6"/>λησεν. θαυμάζω δὲ ὅτι εἰς μὲν ἔλαιον 

    <lb n="7"/>τὸ τοσοῦτο ἀργύριον ἐχώρησαι. ἓξ <num value="6"/> δὶς <choice><corr>ἔβα-

    <lb n="8"/>λες</corr><sic>εβαλας</sic></choice>· ἐνθάδε γὰρ τὸ Ἀμμωνιακὸν <expan><ex cert="high">δραχμῶν</ex></expan> <num value="220">σκ</num>,

    <lb n="9"/>τὸ δὲ Αὐαστικὸν <expan><ex cert="high">δραχμῶν</ex></expan> <num value="200">σ</num>· ὅθεν <choice><corr>εἰ</corr><sic>η</sic></choice> εἰς ἄλλην 

    <lb n="10"/><choice><corr>χρείαν</corr><sic>χριαν</sic></choice> <choice><corr>λαμβάνεις</corr><sic>λαμμβανις</sic></choice> δυναμένην ἡμᾶς 

    <lb n="11"/>ὠφελῆσαι, καλῶς ποιεῖς. ἔγραψας δέ μοι 

    <lb n="12"/>ὡς ἐμοῦ σε κατακόπτοντος ἄποντα, 

    <lb n="13"/>καὶ τοῦτο δὲ χείρω τῶν πρώτων. εἰ 

    <lb n="14"/>γὰρ ἀπαρτὶ ἐπίστασαί μου τὴν γνώμην, 

    <lb n="15"/>οὐκ <choice><corr>ὀφείλεις</corr><sic>οφιλις</sic></choice> ἄνθρωπος κρίνεσθαι. καὶ ἄλλο-

    <lb n="16"/>τέ σοι ἔγραψα ὅτι οὔτ᾽ ἐγὼ τὸν κάμηλον 

    <lb n="17"/>Ἑρμία κατέσχον οὔτε ἄλλου τινός. εἰ δὲ 

    <lb n="18"/>ταῦτα <choice><corr>θέλεις</corr><sic>θελις</sic></choice> με <choice><corr>γράφειν</corr><sic>γραφιν</sic></choice>, γράφω σοι. τάχα γὰρ 

    <lb n="19"/>οὐκ <choice><corr>ἀναγιγνώσκεις</corr><sic>αναγινωσκις</sic></choice> ἅ σοι γράφω. ὅσα δὲ 

    <lb n="20"/><choice><corr>ἔπαθον</corr><sic>επαθαν</sic></choice> ἐνθάδε χάριν τῶν καμήλων 

    <lb n="21"/>τῆς Κόπτου ὅ τε Ἀμμωνᾶς καὶ ὁ αὐτομα-

    <lb n="22"/>τάρις Ἀνθρωπᾶς καὶ οἱ ἄλλοι πάντες δύ-

    <lb n="23"/>νασαι ἀκοῦσαι ἀπὸ τοῦ ἀδελφοῦ σου. οἱ 

    <lb n="24"/>δὲ <choice><corr>τάυροι</corr><sic>ταμροι</sic></choice> σου οἱ κατάρατοι στρηνιῶσι 

    <lb n="25"/>καὶ πολλὰ ὑπὲρ αὐτῶν <choice><corr>προῆλθον</corr><sic>προηλθα</sic></choice> χά<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ρ</unclear>ιν 

    <lb n="26"/>σοῦ. ἐὰ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ν </supplied><gap extent="10" reason="lost" unit="character"/><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="character"/><gap extent="3" reason="lost" unit="character"/><gap extent="4" reason="illegible" unit="character"/><gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="character"/> 

    <lb n="27"/><gap extent="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/><gap extent="4" reason="illegible" unit="character"/> βουλὴν ἔχω, ἐρῶ σοι. ἵνα μὴ δοκῶ 

    <lb n="28"/>πολλὰ <choice><corr>γράφειν</corr><sic>γραφιν</sic></choice>, ἐρρῶσθαί σε <choice><corr><supplied cert="high" reason="omitted">εὔ</supplied>χομαι</corr><sic>χομαι</sic></choice>. 

    <lb n="29,ms" rend="perpendicular"/> τὸν τυφλὸν ὁ ἀδελφός σου <choice><corr>ἠνάγκασέ</corr><sic>ανηκασαι</sic></choice> <choice><corr>με</corr><sic>μαι</sic></choice> πωλῆσαι· 
</ab></div><div n="v" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="30"/>Ἀρτεμᾷ <expan>π<ex cert="high">αρὰ</ex></expan> Ἀπολλωνίου. </ab></div></div><div n="meta.30385" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="description"><p><rs cert="high" type="material">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.30385" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="textDate" type="commentary"><p><date notAfter="300" notBefore="201" type="textDate">III</date></p></div><div n="meta.30385" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="principalEdition" type="bibliography"><listBibl default="NO"><bibl default="NO" subtype="principal" type="publication"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Oxy.</title><biblScope type="volume">36</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">2783</biblScope></bibl><bibl default="NO" type="Trismegistos"><biblScope type="numbers">30385</biblScope></bibl><bibl default="NO" type="DDbDP"><series>0181</series>; <biblScope type="volume">36</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">2783</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" href="0181;36;2783" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" type="Perseus">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.30385" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="corrections" type="bibliography"><head>BL-Einträge nach BL-Konkordanz</head><listBibl default="NO"><bibl default="NO" type="BL"><biblScope type="volume">VIII</biblScope>, S. <biblScope type="pages">262</biblScope></bibl><bibl default="NO" type="BL"><biblScope type="volume">IX</biblScope>, S. <biblScope type="pages">197</biblScope></bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.30385" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="illustrations" type="bibliography"><p>keine</p></div><div n="meta.30385" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="otherPublications" type="bibliography"><head>Andere Publikation</head><bibl default="NO" subtype="other" type="publication">Tibiletti, Lettere private 9</bibl></div><div n="meta.30385" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="translations" type="bibliog